{"id":"1103.1567","submitter":"Hanfeng Li","authors":"Nhan-Phu Chung and Hanfeng Li","title":"Homoclinic groups, IE groups, and expansive algebraic actions","comments":"Minor changes. To appear in Invent. Math","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS math.OA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We give algebraic characterizations for expansiveness of algebraic actions of\ncountable groups. The notion of p-expansiveness is introduced for algebraic\nactions, and we show that for countable amenable groups, a finitely presented\nalgebraic action is 1-expansive exactly when it has finite entropy. We also\nstudy the local entropy theory for actions of countable amenable groups on\ncompact groups by automorphisms, and show that the IE group determines the\nPinsker factor for such actions. For an expansive algebraic action of a\npolycyclic-by-finite group on X, it is shown that the entropy of the action is\nequal to the entropy of the induced action on the Pontryagin dual of the\nhomoclinic group, the homoclinic group is a dense subgroup of the IE group, the\nhomoclinic group is nontrivial exactly when the action has positive entropy,\nand the homoclinic group is dense in X exactly when the action has completely\npositive entropy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Mar 2011 15:58:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2012 03:12:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Apr 2014 12:34:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-17"}
